<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1239: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-27T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 27,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 28—10:21
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>33. Urge draft of loan law be sent by cable as Haitian Government willing
                            to put through law at once and my opinion is that it should be put
                            through before election on April 10th.</p>
                        <p>Am awaiting answer to my 32 March 23, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>